column37: He's got better with each of his four runs, finishing second in Newbury novice (7f, good to firm) last month before convincing nursery win at Doncaster (7f, good to soft); it's possible the slow ground helped last time and he's set to be back on a better surface today, but he's respected nevertheless.

column20: 4/5 Palladium, 7/2 Live Your Dream, 10/1 Spirit Mixer,  Strassia, 12/1 East India Dock,  Lavender Hill Mob, 20/1 Miss Alpilles
column36: 8lb rise for Chester Cup win found him out in top staying handicaps since; bit to find
column37: One of the top juvenile hurdlers last season and he justified warm favouritism when returned to the Flat for the Chester Cup (2m2f) in May; respectable efforts off 8lb higher when sixth of 20 in the Ascot Stakes and Northumberland Plate in June; freshened up since; needs improvement to win at this level.

column4: Jockey Club Rose Bowl Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 4/5 Palladium, 7/2 Live Your Dream, 10/1 Spirit Mixer,  Strassia, 12/1 East India Dock,  Lavender Hill Mob, 20/1 Miss Alpilles
column36: 1m4f course handicap win in May but found out in stronger handicaps since; off 89 days
column37: Career-best effort on the Flat when bagging a 1m4f course handicap (good) in May; found out off higher marks in the Copper Horse at Royal Ascot and Northumberland Plate at Newcastle the following month; in common with stablemate East India Rock, he's been given a three-month break ahead of this step up to Listed company; has something to find on form with a couple of these.

column4: Jockey Club Rose Bowl Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 4/5 Palladium, 7/2 Live Your Dream, 10/1 Spirit Mixer,  Strassia, 12/1 East India Dock,  Lavender Hill Mob, 20/1 Miss Alpilles
column36: Off two years but has gone well after long absence before; player if retaining his ability
column37: Really smart handicapper who won the valuable 1m6f event at the July meeting here in 2021 and 2023; even better form when third of 22 to Absurde in the 2023 Ebor at York (1m6f, good to firm); not seen since finishing a respectable fifth in German Group 1 in September of that year but has gone well after a long absence before; a threat to all if retaining his old ability.

column4: Jockey Club Rose Bowl Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 4/5 Palladium, 7/2 Live Your Dream, 10/1 Spirit Mixer,  Strassia, 12/1 East India Dock,  Lavender Hill Mob, 20/1 Miss Alpilles
column36: Easy win on heavy latest but peak RPR achieved on good to firm; the one to beat
column37: Last year's German Derby winner who was successful in his only hurdle race for Nicky Henderson in January; has done well back on the Flat for this yard since, easily regaining the winning thread in 1m6f Salisbury conditions event on heavy ground 13 days ago, his first outing since being gelded; while all his wins have been achieved on softer than good his peak RPR came when fourth in the Group 2 Hardwicke on good to firm so he doesn't need the mud to be flying; the one to beat.

column4: Jockey Club Rose Bowl Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 4/5 Palladium, 7/2 Live Your Dream, 10/1 Spirit Mixer,  Strassia, 12/1 East India Dock,  Lavender Hill Mob, 20/1 Miss Alpilles
column36: Two valuable 2m handicap wins this year but bit to find on form with a couple here
column37: Held on determinedly in the Northumberland Plate in June and bagged a second valuable 2m handicap success of the year when leading late on at Chester (good to soft) 12 days ago; should give another good account but would struggle to live with an on-song Palladium and/or Live Your Dream.

column4: Jockey Club Rose Bowl Stakes (Listed Race)

column37: Won 1m4f Listed race and third in 1m7f Group 2 (both soft) in France last autumn but seen only twice this year, latterly trailing throughout in the Park Hill at Doncaster on her recent yard debut; no surprise were this good yard to find the key to her before long but she needs to have come on a lot in a short time.

column4: Budds Horseracing Memorabilia Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 3/1 Secret Beach, 7/2 Shrimp Shady, 9/2 Son Of Man, 8/1 Kate O'Riley, 9/1 Houstonn,  My Kinda Ghaiy, 10/1 First Officer, 12/1 Burj Zabeel, 14/1 Chaos Control
column36: 0-10 in handicaps and below par last twice; others are more persuasive
column37: 0-10 in handicaps; twice third over 1m4f at Ascot this year but last two efforts have been below par; dropped another 3lb but it's not enough to tempt.

column4: Budds Horseracing Memorabilia Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 3/1 Secret Beach, 7/2 Shrimp Shady, 9/2 Son Of Man, 8/1 Kate O'Riley, 9/1 Houstonn,  My Kinda Ghaiy, 10/1 First Officer, 12/1 Burj Zabeel, 14/1 Chaos Control

column37: Half-sister to star stayer Big Orange; made steady progress (including Wolverhampton AW wins over 8.6f and 1m4f) until tailed off in a July Course Listed event ten weeks ago; has subsequently switched from Michael Bell to the prolific James Owen yard; could bounce back with a bang.

column4: Budds Horseracing Memorabilia Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 3/1 Secret Beach, 7/2 Shrimp Shady, 9/2 Son Of Man, 8/1 Kate O'Riley, 9/1 Houstonn,  My Kinda Ghaiy, 10/1 First Officer, 12/1 Burj Zabeel, 14/1 Chaos Control

column37: Had a good year, including a breakthrough win at York (1m4f, good to firm) in July; creditable second at Chester (extended 1m4f, good) 12 days ago and a 2lb nudge shouldn't prevent a prominent showing.

column4: Budds Horseracing Memorabilia Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 3/1 Secret Beach, 7/2 Shrimp Shady, 9/2 Son Of Man, 8/1 Kate O'Riley, 9/1 Houstonn,  My Kinda Ghaiy, 10/1 First Officer, 12/1 Burj Zabeel, 14/1 Chaos Control
column36: Recent efforts nothing special but back on the mark he defied on July Course in summer
column37: Beat three rivals over 1m4f on the July Course here (good to firm) under Alexandra Egan in midsummer; comfortably held in three outings since but has dipped back to that successful mark.

column4: Budds Horseracing Memorabilia Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 3/1 Secret Beach, 7/2 Shrimp Shady, 9/2 Son Of Man, 8/1 Kate O'Riley, 9/1 Houstonn,  My Kinda Ghaiy, 10/1 First Officer, 12/1 Burj Zabeel, 14/1 Chaos Control
column36: Maiden win in June but beaten upwards of 4l in three handicaps since
column37: 1m4f maiden winner on good in June beaten but upwards of 4l in his three handicaps since; being eased another 2lb can only help but others are still preferred.

column4: Budds Horseracing Memorabilia Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 3/1 Secret Beach, 7/2 Shrimp Shady, 9/2 Son Of Man, 8/1 Kate O'Riley, 9/1 Houstonn,  My Kinda Ghaiy, 10/1 First Officer, 12/1 Burj Zabeel, 14/1 Chaos Control
column36: Did well over hurdles last summer but not seen since; betting should guide
column37: Won a 1m6f AW handicap off 1lb higher on his yard debut in November 2022; better known as a quite useful handicap hurdler since but he hasn't been seen since finishing a creditable third at Perth in August 2024; chance he'll be using this as a prep ahead of a return to hurdles but the betting is perhaps the best guide to expectations.

column4: Budds Horseracing Memorabilia Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 3/1 Secret Beach, 7/2 Shrimp Shady, 9/2 Son Of Man, 8/1 Kate O'Riley, 9/1 Houstonn,  My Kinda Ghaiy, 10/1 First Officer, 12/1 Burj Zabeel, 14/1 Chaos Control
column36: Turf win last autumn; well-held third in AW novice on return but retains potential
column37: Had quite useful subsequent winners behind when winning a 1m Windsor novice (good to firm) last September; not seen again until 13l third in a 1m4f Kempton novice last month but the fact he went off at 6-5 suggests better was expected by his leading stable, and he retains obvious potential for handicaps.

column4: Budds Horseracing Memorabilia Handicap (GBBPlus Race)
column20: 3/1 Secret Beach, 7/2 Shrimp Shady, 9/2 Son Of Man, 8/1 Kate O'Riley, 9/1 Houstonn,  My Kinda Ghaiy, 10/1 First Officer, 12/1 Burj Zabeel, 14/1 Chaos Control

column37: Bred to come into his own over middle distances but couldn't find improvement on his first attempt at a longer trip when fifth on 1m4f Chester handicap debut with cheekpieces added back in May; off since and the headgear is left off on return; still early days.

column37: Kicked off campaign with two 1m wins (good to firm) and he's below his last winning mark; however, his form has been patchy since he went close at Wetherby in June and he needs to get back on track.

column4: Rogues Gallery Racing Syndicate Handicap

column37: His form can be up and down but he bolted up at Salisbury (1m, good to firm) last month and ran pretty well behind two 3yos when third at Newbury (1m, good) last time; might not be far away.

column4: Rogues Gallery Racing Syndicate Handicap

column4: Rogues Gallery Racing Syndicate Handicap

column37: Ran well in first-time cheekpieces at Hamilton (1m, good) in July and returned to form in a first-time visor when beaten just a neck at Musselburgh (1m, good to soft) recently; it remains to be seen if the visor will maintain its effect but he's a player if backing up that latest performance.

column37: Made it 0-7 when below par at Newbury four weeks ago, when failing to settle; however, prior to that he went close in a small field at Salisbury (1m, good to firm) and can be in the picture if leaving last time behind.

column37: 9yo who is without a win since October 2023 and displayed mixed form last winter, when last seen; however, he's dropped to a dangerous mark and has often running well following a break; interesting contender.

column37: Nine-race maiden who hasn't progressed but there have been encouraging signs with these cheekpieces applied on his last two runs (1m/8.5f, soft); showed promise on fast ground last June; possible contender.

column37: Lightly raced 3yo who was a very close third of seven at Doncaster (1m, good to firm) last month and again finished third at Redcar (1m, good) last Tuesday, behind comfortably winner Just Typical who now carries a 5lb penalty; could be thereabouts.

column37: Irish point winner; showed promise in both maiden hurdles at Ayr, particularly the latest (upped to 2m3f, heavy) when keeping on for third in a fair race; has more to offer.

column37: Reversed previous C&D form with King Roly under an aggressive front-running ride from Sean Bowen here 17 days ago (good); that wasn't without the occasional scare over his fences but he's clearly capable of going well again off just 4lb higher.

column37: Only his second run over fences and visored for the first time when making all for an 11l success over C&D in April (good to soft); the handicapper didn't hold back with an 11lb rise but this 7yo could still be ahead of the game; does lack a run though and some of his rivals are race-fit.

column37: Progressive over hurdles last season in winning two 2m handicaps (on soft) and his following defeats were no backward steps (on good to soft and good); has a career-high mark to deal with but might well improve again for fences.

column37: Irish point winner who has had little racing for a 7yo; placed in a 2m4f handicap hurdle here before finishing fourth over C&D on his chase debut when left behind by Lightkeeper and King Roly; asking plenty of him to reverse placings with both of those.
